15 WHEREAS, her bright spirit extended beyond her home as she was ever-present with her
16 parents at community coat drives and hearings, a testament to the impact she had even in her
17 earliest days; and
18 WHEREAS, Khari Oramae Burns departed this life suddenly on March 8, 2024, leaving
19 behind a legacy of warmth, love, and happiness that continues to shine in the hearts of those
20 who were blessed to know her; and
21 WHEREAS, though she left this world too soon, her memory lives on through her devoted
22 parents, Erik Sr. and Brittany; her loving brother, Erik Jr.; her maternal grandmother, Pamela
23 Jones; her paternal grandparents, Doris Burns and Billy Burns; her uncle, Eugene Burns; and
24 a host of cherished cousins, aunts, uncles, family members, and friends.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Khari Oramae Burns and
27 express their deepest and most sincere regret at her passing.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body recognize March 8, 2025, as
29 Infant Emergency Awareness Day.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 family of Khari Oramae Burns.
